1
00:00:00,750 --> 00:00:05,481
Here’s what I’ve learned after 1 full
month of studying and back testing the Elliot

2
00:00:05,481 --> 00:00:09,800
Wave Theory.
The key to using the Elliot method successfully

3
00:00:09,800 --> 00:00:14,580
lies in counting the waves correctly and identifying
the wave in which the market is currently

4
00:00:14,580 --> 00:00:19,760
trading in. That’s it. Identify the wave
and you will profit from it.

5
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:24,480
Today, I will try to help you better understand
the general characteristics of the different

6
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:29,840
waves within the overall market structure.
Learn this, and Elliot Wave theory will become

7
00:00:29,840 --> 00:00:33,460
much simpler.
Before we begin, if you want more videos,

8
00:00:33,460 --> 00:00:38,170
more often, please drop a like to help us
with Youtube algorithm and turn on the bell,

9
00:00:38,170 --> 00:00:41,190
so you don’t miss when new content is released.

10
00:00:41,190 --> 00:00:45,470
One of the key points within the Elliott wave
theory is the concept of the fractal nature

11
00:00:45,470 --> 00:00:51,040
of the markets. This means price patterns
repeat themselves over and over again on all

12
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:54,700
time frames.
Under the Elliott wave theory, there are two

13
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:59,340
types of price progressions.
The first are those price movements or waves

14
00:00:59,340 --> 00:01:04,580
that are aligned with the larger trend. These
price movements are referred to as motive

15
00:01:04,580 --> 00:01:07,570
waves.
The second are those price movements are waves

16
00:01:07,570 --> 00:01:12,790
that are contrary to the larger trend. These
price movements are referred to as corrective

17
00:01:12,790 --> 00:01:14,910
waves.

18
00:01:14,910 --> 00:01:20,210
Motive waves can be classified further as
impulse waves or diagonal waves depending

19
00:01:20,210 --> 00:01:24,310
on the form and location within the overall
structure.

20
00:01:24,310 --> 00:01:29,090
Impulse waves are the most common form of
motive waves and the easiest to spot in a

21
00:01:29,090 --> 00:01:32,710
market
A diagonal wave also moves the market in the

22
00:01:32,710 --> 00:01:37,359
direction of the trend. The difference is
that the diagonal wave looks like a wedge

23
00:01:37,359 --> 00:01:42,810
- either expanding or contracting.
Corrective waves are generally classified

24
00:01:42,810 --> 00:01:51,200
as either flat structures, zigzag structures,
triangle structures, or double or triple combinations.

25
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:56,520
The basic form of the entire Elliott wave
sequence is comprised of five waves that make

26
00:01:56,520 --> 00:02:00,939
up the motive wave, which are labeled waves
one through five.

27
00:02:00,939 --> 00:02:05,540
Following the completion of wave five within
the motive sequence, the market will develop

28
00:02:05,540 --> 00:02:11,120
into a three wave retracement that moves contrary
to this motive wave sequence.

29
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:17,879
This retracement move consists of three waves
labeled as waves A, B and C.

30
00:02:17,879 --> 00:02:22,489
If you’re just starting, there are only
three unbreakable rules as it relates to the

31
00:02:22,489 --> 00:02:27,130
Elliott wave principle.
The first rule is that wave two cannot retrace

32
00:02:27,130 --> 00:02:32,700
more than 100% of wave one.
The second rule is that wave four cannot move

33
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:38,370
into the territory of wave one.
And finally, wave three cannot be the shortest

34
00:02:38,370 --> 00:02:42,130
wave amongst waves one, three, and five.

35
00:02:42,130 --> 00:02:47,069
So, like I said in the beginning of the video,
if you learn to recognize the current wave

36
00:02:47,069 --> 00:02:52,110
of the market, you will be ahead of most traders.
Now let’s me share the characteristics of

37
00:02:52,110 --> 00:02:57,170
the various waves within the Elliott wave
structure, in the context of a bull market.

38
00:02:57,170 --> 00:03:01,730
Pay attention to each description, and by
the end of the video Elliot wave theory will

39
00:03:01,730 --> 00:03:04,920
no longer appear complicated.

40
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:10,430
Wave one begins the impulse sequence.
During this wave prices began to bounce higher

41
00:03:10,430 --> 00:03:15,319
after a long sustained downtrend.
The sentiment in the market is very bearish

42
00:03:15,319 --> 00:03:19,900
at the start of wave one.
As wave one moves higher, most people see

43
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:25,180
this upside price movement as just a bear
market rally, and many investors and traders

44
00:03:25,180 --> 00:03:30,650
consider wave one as a good opportunity to
initiate a new short position or add to their

45
00:03:30,650 --> 00:03:33,660
existing short positions.

46
00:03:33,660 --> 00:03:39,380
Wave one is generally the least predictive
wave within the entire Elliott wave structure.

47
00:03:39,380 --> 00:03:42,970
There is really no way to know how long the
wave will last.

48
00:03:42,970 --> 00:03:48,900
However, at some point it will become clearly
apparent that wave one has ended, as a significant

49
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:55,070
swing high is reached, and prices begin to
move lower in a bearish direction once again.

50
00:03:55,070 --> 00:04:00,290
Wave one generally subdivides into five smaller
waves and can sometimes appear as a leading

51
00:04:00,290 --> 00:04:03,159
diagonal structure.

52
00:04:03,159 --> 00:04:07,489
After wave one completes, the next one in
the sequence will be wave two.

53
00:04:07,489 --> 00:04:13,130
Wave two will move counter to wave one, and
will retrace a large portion of wave one.

54
00:04:13,130 --> 00:04:20,519
Often wave two will retrace wave one by either
a 50% retracement, 61% retracement, or even

55
00:04:20,519 --> 00:04:25,530
78% retracement.
During wave two investors and traders begin

56
00:04:25,530 --> 00:04:31,160
to feel assured once again that the downtrend
has continued. However, the market will fail

57
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:33,310
to break below the wave one low.

58
00:04:33,310 --> 00:04:39,140
Remember, one of the unbreakable rules within
the Elliott wave theory, which is, that wave

59
00:04:39,140 --> 00:04:42,800
two cannot retrace below the start of wave
one.

60
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:47,250
Informed traders will begin to recognize this
pattern and start to position to the long

61
00:04:47,250 --> 00:04:50,872
side of the market.
Wave two will generally take the form of a

62
00:04:50,872 --> 00:04:56,000
zigzag correction, or a flat correction.
In either case the retracement will be fairly

63
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:59,530
deep.
Additionally, since wave two is a corrective

64
00:04:59,530 --> 00:05:05,810
structure, it will develop as an ABC pattern
comprised of three waves.

65
00:05:05,810 --> 00:05:10,780
Wave three offers the largest potential for
profit as it is usually the biggest and most

66
00:05:10,780 --> 00:05:14,440
powerful wave within the overall Elliott wave
structure.

67
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:19,610
The psychology of traders during wave three
is generally one of growing optimism.

68
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:24,330
Although many of the earlier sellers will
still resist the optimistic outlook during

69
00:05:24,330 --> 00:05:29,320
the early stages of wave three, it will become
increasingly evident to most traders that

70
00:05:29,320 --> 00:05:33,400
the trend has shifted, and the markets are
poised to move higher.

71
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:38,550
After the break of the swing high of wave
one, prices will begin to accelerate upward

72
00:05:38,550 --> 00:05:44,620
as more and more traders recognize the bullish
sentiment and start taking long positions.

73
00:05:44,620 --> 00:05:49,979
Additionally, many sellers will have their
stops triggered at the wave one swing high,

74
00:05:49,979 --> 00:05:54,500
which adds further fuel to the upper price
momentum.

75
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:59,390
If you identify the 3rd wave, you need to
join the trend as quickly as possible in order

76
00:05:59,390 --> 00:06:04,669
to take advantage of the explosive moves that
are characteristic of wave three.

77
00:06:04,669 --> 00:06:09,639
Those that wait for a pullback or retracement
to get in, will often miss the entire move,

78
00:06:09,639 --> 00:06:14,871
as wave three offers very little in the way
of pullbacks, and when they are present, they

79
00:06:14,871 --> 00:06:20,699
tend to be quite shallow.
Wave three will often travel 1.618 times the

80
00:06:20,699 --> 00:06:26,250
length of wave one measured from the end of
wave two. The second most common projection

81
00:06:26,250 --> 00:06:32,880
for wave three is for it to travel 2.618 times
the length of wave one measured from the end

82
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:36,389
of wave two.
One of the guidelines within the Elliott wave

83
00:06:36,389 --> 00:06:42,470
principle is that among waves 1,3 and 5 of
the impulse sequence, there will be one extended

84
00:06:42,470 --> 00:06:45,880
wave which is quite larger than the other
two.

85
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:50,820
In most cases, wave 3 will be that extended
wave.

86
00:06:50,820 --> 00:06:55,290
Wave four will follow wave three and will
retrace a portion of wave three.

87
00:06:55,290 --> 00:07:02,949
Typically, wave four will be a shallower retracement,
and will often terminate at 38% or 50% of

88
00:07:02,949 --> 00:07:06,550
wave three.
Since wave three is often the longest wave

89
00:07:06,550 --> 00:07:11,710
within the overall sequence, we can expect
wave four to be less aggressive in percentage

90
00:07:11,710 --> 00:07:16,250
terms than wave two.
Also, we need to keep in mind one of the core

91
00:07:16,250 --> 00:07:22,240
rules within the Elliott wave theory during
wave four. That is wave four should not overlap

92
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:26,900
into the territory of wave one.
If it does, then you need to relabel your

93
00:07:26,900 --> 00:07:31,230
wave count as this is an unbreakable rule.

94
00:07:31,230 --> 00:07:34,680
Wave four is also often seen as a profit-taking
wave.

95
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:38,449
Because those traders that bought early in
wave three are sitting on a healthy amount

96
00:07:38,449 --> 00:07:44,150
of profits, many of these traders will begin
to liquidate their positions and lock in their

97
00:07:44,150 --> 00:07:47,610
profits.
This creates a sideways price movement that

98
00:07:47,610 --> 00:07:52,830
is often prolonged in nature.
Wave four often takes the form of a triangle.

99
00:07:52,830 --> 00:07:58,740
However, wave four can also be a flat formation,
and sometimes it forms as a zigzag pattern

100
00:07:58,740 --> 00:08:01,289
or some combination.

101
00:08:01,289 --> 00:08:06,180
The price action often appears range bound,
with prices moving back and forth without

102
00:08:06,180 --> 00:08:09,930
any clear direction.
Wave four brings with it whipsawing price

103
00:08:09,930 --> 00:08:14,770
action that often generates false breakout
on either side of the market.

104
00:08:14,770 --> 00:08:19,180
You need to be very careful when taking new
positions during wave four as you are more

105
00:08:19,180 --> 00:08:24,889
likely to lose money during these directionless
market conditions.

106
00:08:24,889 --> 00:08:29,340
Wave five is the final leg within the Elliott
wave impulse sequence.

107
00:08:29,340 --> 00:08:34,709
It moves in the direction of the overall trend
similarly to waves one, and wave three.

108
00:08:34,709 --> 00:08:38,750
During the progression of wave five, almost
everyone is bullish.

109
00:08:38,750 --> 00:08:43,940
Wave five is often considered a retail wave,
because it is during this time when most retail

110
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:49,970
investors are driving prices higher, often
to extreme valuations.

111
00:08:49,970 --> 00:08:54,910
The momentum behind the bullish activity in
wave five will be less dynamic than that during

112
00:08:54,910 --> 00:08:58,820
the wave three progression.
This basically means that the velocity of

113
00:08:58,820 --> 00:09:03,890
the price movement will be more subdued than
that seen during wave three.

114
00:09:03,890 --> 00:09:09,160
During the late stages of wave five we will
also see technical divergence patterns form

115
00:09:09,160 --> 00:09:15,980
between the price action and many momentum
indicators such as RSI, Stochastics, and MACD.

116
00:09:15,980 --> 00:09:20,621
These momentum divergence signals are telling
us is that the velocity of the price movement

117
00:09:20,621 --> 00:09:26,750
higher is diminishing, and we should expect
the upside trend to reverse its course soon.

118
00:09:26,750 --> 00:09:32,050
Along with momentum divergences, wave five
will often register lower volume compared

119
00:09:32,050 --> 00:09:37,110
to wave three. This is another indication
that the trend is weakening and that profits

120
00:09:37,110 --> 00:09:41,130
should be locked in, as a potential reversal
is imminent.

121
00:09:41,130 --> 00:09:46,440
In terms of how far wave five will travel,
well…wave five will terminate upon reaching

122
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:51,030
a length that is equivalent to the length
seen in wave one.

123
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:56,920
The next most likely projection for wave five
is for it to travel a distance of 61% the

124
00:09:56,920 --> 00:10:02,310
length of wave one. Both of these projections
for wave five are measured from the end of

125
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:04,640
wave four.

126
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:09,420
The end of wave five brings with it the completion
of the impulse sequence.

127
00:10:09,420 --> 00:10:14,860
More specifically, the impulse sequence consists
of waves one through five, and thus, at the

128
00:10:14,860 --> 00:10:19,660
end of wave five, we can expect a corrective
structure to follow which will often be a

129
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:24,320
three wave pattern, waves A, B, and C.

130
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:29,160
Wave A starts the corrective sequence and
during this phase, most traders are still

131
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:34,830
very bullish, and consider the wave A pullback
as just another minor retracement.

132
00:10:34,830 --> 00:10:38,420
Wave A is somewhat similar to wave one in
its structure.

133
00:10:38,420 --> 00:10:42,880
During both of these wave progressions, the
market participants are heavily positioned

134
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:47,180
on one side of the market, depending on the
direction of the larger trend.

135
00:10:47,180 --> 00:10:52,500
However, just as in wave one, some experienced
traders begin to recognize the overbought

136
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:58,600
market condition during wave five.
Wave A is often a sharp move and may subdivide

137
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:03,680
as either a five wave pattern or a three wave
pattern.

138
00:11:03,680 --> 00:11:08,420
Wave B is the second leg of the corrective
structure and follows wave A.

139
00:11:08,420 --> 00:11:14,250
Wave B is often considered a bull trap, because
it tends to draw in a lot of traders, believing

140
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:19,839
that the existing trend is still healthy.
However, this is far from the case. Wave B

141
00:11:19,839 --> 00:11:24,930
will be a fairly short-lived pattern and will
often fail to surpass the wave five swing

142
00:11:24,930 --> 00:11:26,960
high.

143
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:31,870
Wave B will often create a double top formation
in which it will try to test the wave five

144
00:11:31,870 --> 00:11:36,440
extreme and fail to breach it.
This doesn’t always happen; however, it

145
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:42,350
is quite characteristic for wave B to terminate
just short of the wave five extreme.

146
00:11:42,350 --> 00:11:49,670
Wave B is often a fairly deep retracement
and will retrace wave A by either 50%, 61%,

147
00:11:49,670 --> 00:11:54,710
or 78%.
The subdivision within Wave B itself is often

148
00:11:54,710 --> 00:12:00,200
seen as a zigzag pattern, but sometimes it
will form as a triangle as well.

149
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:04,700
One of the best trades within the Elliott
wave sequence is to fade the wave B price

150
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:08,990
move as it nears its terminal point.

151
00:12:08,990 --> 00:12:14,529
After wave B completes, wave C will begin
and this wave marks the final leg within the

152
00:12:14,529 --> 00:12:19,320
entire corrective structure.
When the wave B swing low is breached, that

153
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:24,149
event will mark a turning point where more
and more traders will become convinced that

154
00:12:24,149 --> 00:12:34,100
the uptrend has actually ended, and the market
is poised for lower prices.

155
00:12:34,100 --> 00:12:44,290
Wave 
C is often equivalent to the length of wave

156
00:12:44,290 --> 00:12:48,709
A.
Wave C will travel a distance of 1.27 times

157
00:12:48,709 --> 00:12:53,070
the length of wave A.
After this distance, the next most likely

158
00:12:53,070 --> 00:12:59,680
area for wave C to terminate would be when
it has traveled the distance of 1.61 times

159
00:12:59,680 --> 00:13:02,470
the length the wave A.

160
00:13:02,470 --> 00:13:07,450
Now that you know the characteristics of each
wave, let me share a simple checklist to apply

161
00:13:07,450 --> 00:13:12,990
to the sequence. Print it or write it down,
and use it every time you are unsure about

162
00:13:12,990 --> 00:13:19,070
the current wave of the market.
• Wave 1, wave 3 and wave 5 are trending.

163
00:13:19,070 --> 00:13:26,980
• Wave 2 and wave 4 are corrections.
• Of wave 1, wave 3 and wave 5, wave 3 must

164
00:13:26,980 --> 00:13:29,880
not be the shortest, but it does not have
to be the longest

165
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:35,509
• Wave 2 can retrace up to 99 percent of
wave 1.

166
00:13:35,509 --> 00:13:39,600
• Wave 4 should not go into the price area
of wave 2.

167
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:44,199
• Wave 4 never enters the price territory
of wave 1

168
00:13:44,199 --> 00:13:50,320
• Wave 2 and wave 4 must display alternation
in as many ways as possible. That is, wave

169
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:55,700
2 and wave 4 must be different in as many
ways as possible.

170
00:13:55,700 --> 00:14:01,350
Alternation occurs between wave 2 and wave
4 as either price, time or pattern type.

171
00:14:01,350 --> 00:14:08,700
• Price: Wave 2 when compared to wave 4
may be obviously smaller/larger in price.

172
00:14:08,700 --> 00:14:15,510
• Time: Wave 2 when compared to wave 4 may
take much more/less time.

173
00:14:15,510 --> 00:14:22,430
• Pattern: Wave 2 may be a simple ABC. Wave
4 could be a more complex A B C or even a

174
00:14:22,430 --> 00:16:31,940
triangle. Wave 2 could be a flat formation.
Wave 4 could be a zigzag or vice versa.

